1.5
) and internarial distance (IN 
1.8
); nostril closer to tip of snout (NS 1.0) than eye (EN 
1.4
); tympanum indistinct or obscured by a layer of skin without clearly defined borders, supratympanic fold distinct, extending from posterior corner of upper eyelid to near the insertion of forelimb at axilla; eye diameter (EL 
2.3
); vomerine ridge absent; tongue elliptical. Forelimbs moderately short and thin; forelimb (
FAL
5.1
) shorter than hand length (
HAL
6.0); fingers short, finger length formula I<IV<II<III; tips of all fingers without discs, rounded; subarticular tubercles prominent, rounded, all present (

Fig. 
1

); palmar tubercles three, well developed, oval. Hindlimbs relatively long and thin, thigh length (
